text: Obb-ha-dee hoon, friend. Materials you've brought are so good that clothes almost make themselves!
Glad I could help!
Shukriyaa, friend. See? I can do that too!
They don't look that good in pictures, though... I'm afraid that can skew opinions even before the show starts.
Don't worry! I have a trick I learned from one girl and her dog... You just need better lighting!
I'm so thankful, friend. My participation in the show is confirmed!
Wheee! Told ya!
They'll have a banquet, and I offered to deliver food myself, so that it matches the clothes.
Good thinking. Everything in harmony, right?
Do you need help?
Yes.Can you help me, please? I'm so nervous!
You don't have to ask!
Sure! I know all local farmers by face, anyway...
So, um... I googled France, and it turns out that thingies I asked you for were Mexican.
They are ease to mix up, yes.
That was an honest mistake, don't blame yourself!
Oh, thank you... can you bring me another flag-badge? And that tiny funny boat. This time it's french for sure, I checked!
I'll be right back!
That photoset was a bomb! Everyone on the internet liked my little french doggo! They said he's magnified.
Glad to help!
You mean magnifique?
I wonder, will I be able to survive there? Do they... you know... eat food?
Care to find out?
You bet! France is famous for its cuisine!
Awesome! Can you help me arrange a french breakfast?
With pleasure!
Tacos coming right up... Just kidding!
Oh hello! I'm so glaaad to see you again!
How's your preparing for the trip going?
We've just seen each other... Did something happen?
I've been wondering, what if it'll be too cold for Squidger on a plane? He's never flown before, you know...
He's small enough to fly in the cabin... But it can be really chilly there, too.
Will you help me make some clothes for him? Pretty please?
All right, all right.
Yeah, I know a guy who can show us how to sew...
Thank you so much! Everything looks so delicious I'm struggling not to eat it myself.
You're right, I never thought veggies can look so good...
Keep yourself together! Think about the show!
Oh, I talked to my friend Eugene... He said a lot of fresh vegetables could upset stomach of someone who's not quite used to eating them.
That walking, talking encyclopedy... But yeah, he could be right.
What do we do then?
I'm afraid it's better to stack some medicine, just in case. But let's look for natural ones, please?
I think I've seen something herbal in a nearby drugstore.
You don't believe in homeopathy, do you?
We did a lot of good today, achchha aadamee. A lot of energy well-spent. Now let's replenish it with some delicious vegetables, shall we?
I'm so exhausted that I'm ready to eat them with the basket.
-munch-yhweah-munch-crunch!
Dhanyavaad, friend. Wasn't that good? Did you like it?
A lot.
I feel relaxed... And energized! And relaxed... But energized!
